GitHub Actions allows you to automate your software development workflows directly within your GitHub repositories. This can range from simple tasks like running tests and linting code to complex deployments and infrastructure management. It's a powerful tool for CI/CD (Continuous Integration/Continuous Delivery). Since you're already using Git, integrating with GitHub Actions is a natural extension. It also becomes increasingly important as DevOps practices become more common.

ira and Confluence are core tools for Agile and software development teams. Jira helps with project management, issue tracking, and bug fixing. Confluence facilitates collaboration and knowledge sharing through documentation and wikis. Since you're already using Scrum, mastering these tools will make you more effective within your team.   



Git is the industry-standard version control system. It allows you to track changes to your code, collaborate with others, and revert to previous versions if needed. It is fundamental for any software development project.   

VS Code (Visual Studio Code) is a highly popular and versatile code editor.

 It supports a wide range of programming languages and offers features like debugging, IntelliSense (code completion), Git integration, and extensions that can enhance your productivity. Choosing a powerful and extensible code editor is essential for efficient development.
